{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1828,"text":"Today I'm going to speak to you"},{"time":3472,"text":"about the last 30 years\nof architectural history."},{"time":7685,"text":"That's a lot to pack into 18 minutes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":10167,"text":"It's a complex topic,"},{"time":11878,"text":"so we're just going to dive right in\nat a complex place:"},{"time":16276,"text":"New Jersey."},{"time":17506,"text":"Because 30 years ago, I'm from Jersey,"},{"time":20720,"text":"and I was six, and I lived there\nin my parents' house"},{"time":24586,"text":"in a town called Livingston,"},{"time":26234,"text":"and this was my childhood bedroom."},{"time":29689,"text":"Around the corner from my bedroom"},{"time":32148,"text":"was the bathroom\nthat I used to share with my sister."},{"time":35225,"text":"And in between my bedroom and the bathroom"},{"time":38162,"text":"was a balcony that overlooked\nthe family room."},{"time":41413,"text":"And that's where everyone\nwould hang out and watch TV,"},{"time":45119,"text":"so that every time that I walked\nfrom my bedroom to the bathroom,"},{"time":49306,"text":"everyone would see me,"},{"time":50666,"text":"and every time I took a shower\nand would come back in a towel,"},{"time":54444,"text":"everyone would see me."},{"time":56162,"text":"And I looked like this."},{"time":58718,"text":"I was awkward,"},{"time":61765,"text":"insecure, and I hated it."},{"time":63880,"text":"I hated that walk, I hated that balcony,"},{"time":66943,"text":"I hated that room, and I hated that house."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70769,"text":"And that's architecture."},{"time":72917,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":74258,"text":"Done."},{"time":76088,"text":"That feeling, those emotions that I felt,"},{"time":79486,"text":"that's the power of architecture,"},{"time":82203,"text":"because architecture is not about math\nand it's not about zoning,"},{"time":85765,"text":"it's about those visceral,\nemotional connections"},{"time":89147,"text":"that we feel to the places that we occupy."},{"time":92653,"text":"And it's no surprise\nthat we feel that way,"},{"time":95553,"text":"because according to the EPA,"},{"time":97785,"text":"Americans spend 90 percent\nof their time indoors."},{"time":102428,"text":"That's 90 percent of our time\nsurrounded by architecture."},{"time":107188,"text":"That's huge."},{"time":108720,"text":"That means that architecture is shaping us\nin ways that we didn't even realize."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113922,"text":"That makes us a little bit gullible\nand very, very predictable."},{"time":119464,"text":"It means that when I show you\na building like this,"},{"time":122117,"text":"I know what you think:"},{"time":123523,"text":"You think \"power\"\nand \"stability\" and \"democracy.\""},{"time":127239,"text":"And I know you think that\nbecause it's based on a building"},{"time":130896,"text":"that was build 2,500 years ago\nby the Greeks."},{"time":134272,"text":"This is a trick."},{"time":135912,"text":"This is a trigger that architects use"},{"time":138104,"text":"to get you to create\nan emotional connection"},{"time":142017,"text":"to the forms that we build\nour buildings out of."},{"time":145237,"text":"It's a predictable emotional connection,"},{"time":147901,"text":"and we've been using this trick\nfor a long, long time."},{"time":151629,"text":"We used it [200] years ago to build banks."},{"time":154926,"text":"We used it in the 19th century\nto build art museums."},{"time":158107,"text":"And in the 20th century in America,"},{"time":160336,"text":"we used it to build houses."},{"time":162195,"text":"And look at these solid,\nstable little soldiers"},{"time":164957,"text":"facing the ocean\nand keeping away the elements."}]},{"cues":[{"time":168265,"text":"This is really, really useful,"},{"time":170924,"text":"because building things is terrifying."},{"time":174331,"text":"It's expensive, it takes a long time,\nand it's very complicated."},{"time":178996,"text":"And the people that build things --"},{"time":181178,"text":"developers and governments --"},{"time":183407,"text":"they're naturally afraid of innovation,"},{"time":186284,"text":"and they'd rather just use those forms\nthat they know you'll respond to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191125,"text":"That's how we end up\nwith buildings like this."},{"time":194096,"text":"This is a nice building."},{"time":195790,"text":"This is the Livingston Public Library"},{"time":198105,"text":"that was completed in 2004 in my hometown,"},{"time":201239,"text":"and, you know, it's got a dome"},{"time":202888,"text":"and it's got this round thing \nand columns, red brick,"},{"time":206495,"text":"and you can kind of guess what Livingston\nis trying to say with this building:"},{"time":211509,"text":"children, property values and history."},{"time":215751,"text":"But it doesn't have much to do\nwith what a library actually does today."},{"time":220209,"text":"That same year, in 2004,\non the other side of the country,"},{"time":224297,"text":"another library was completed,"},{"time":226316,"text":"and it looks like this."},{"time":227998,"text":"It's in Seattle."},{"time":230140,"text":"This library is about how\nwe consume media in a digital age."},{"time":235718,"text":"It's about a new kind\nof public amenity for the city,"},{"time":239312,"text":"a place to gather and read and share."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243244,"text":"So how is it possible"},{"time":244891,"text":"that in the same year,\nin the same country,"},{"time":248328,"text":"two buildings, both called libraries,"},{"time":250975,"text":"look so completely different?"},{"time":253576,"text":"And the answer is that architecture works\non the principle of a pendulum."},{"time":259501,"text":"On the one side is innovation,"},{"time":262393,"text":"and architects are constantly pushing,\npushing for new technologies,"},{"time":266034,"text":"new typologies, new solutions\nfor the way that we live today."},{"time":269886,"text":"And we push and we push and we push"},{"time":272304,"text":"until we completely alienate all of you."},{"time":274927,"text":"We wear all black, we get very depressed,"},{"time":277177,"text":"you think we're adorable,"},{"time":279362,"text":"we're dead inside because\nwe've got no choice."},{"time":282845,"text":"We have to go to the other side"},{"time":284621,"text":"and reengage those symbols\nthat we know you love."},{"time":288394,"text":"So we do that, and you're happy,"},{"time":290577,"text":"we feel like sellouts,"},{"time":292411,"text":"so we start experimenting again"},{"time":294085,"text":"and we push the pendulum back\nand back and forth and back and forth"},{"time":297303,"text":"we've gone for the last 300 years,"},{"time":299702,"text":"and certainly for the last 30 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302926,"text":"Okay, 30 years ago\nwe were coming out of the '70s."},{"time":306542,"text":"Architects had been busy experimenting\nwith something called brutalism."},{"time":310519,"text":"It's about concrete."},{"time":311789,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":313285,"text":"You can guess this."},{"time":314453,"text":"Small windows, dehumanizing scale."},{"time":317807,"text":"This is really tough stuff."},{"time":320594,"text":"So as we get closer to the '80s,"},{"time":323381,"text":"we start to reengage those symbols."},{"time":325748,"text":"We push the pendulum\nback into the other direction."},{"time":328720,"text":"We take these forms that we know you love"},{"time":331553,"text":"and we update them."},{"time":333142,"text":"We add neon"},{"time":335175,"text":"and we add pastels"},{"time":337463,"text":"and we use new materials."},{"time":339141,"text":"And you love it."},{"time":340603,"text":"And we can't give you enough of it."},{"time":342576,"text":"We take Chippendale armoires"},{"time":344764,"text":"and we turned those into skyscrapers,"},{"time":347160,"text":"and skyscrapers can be\nmedieval castles made out of glass."},{"time":352409,"text":"Forms got big,"},{"time":353985,"text":"forms got bold and colorful."},{"time":356536,"text":"Dwarves became columns."},{"time":359404,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":360467,"text":"Swans grew to the size of buildings."},{"time":362597,"text":"It was crazy."},{"time":364640,"text":"But it's the '80s, it's cool."},{"time":368537,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":369739,"text":"We're all hanging out in malls"},{"time":371757,"text":"and we're all moving to the suburbs,"},{"time":374162,"text":"and out there, out in the suburbs,"},{"time":376760,"text":"we can create our own\narchitectural fantasies."},{"time":380116,"text":"And those fantasies,"},{"time":381894,"text":"they can be Mediterranean"},{"time":383981,"text":"or French"},{"time":385930,"text":"or Italian."},{"time":387154,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":388821,"text":"Possibly with endless breadsticks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390738,"text":"This is the thing about postmodernism."},{"time":392788,"text":"This is the thing about symbols."},{"time":394908,"text":"They're easy, they're cheap,"},{"time":397912,"text":"because instead of making places,"},{"time":400441,"text":"we're making memories of places."},{"time":403091,"text":"Because I know, \nand I know all of you know,"},{"time":405971,"text":"this isn't Tuscany."},{"time":408182,"text":"This is Ohio."},{"time":409452,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":410994,"text":"So architects get frustrated,"},{"time":412843,"text":"and we start pushing the pendulum\nback into the other direction."},{"time":416559,"text":"In the late '80s and early '90s,"},{"time":418810,"text":"we start experimenting with something\ncalled deconstructivism."},{"time":422727,"text":"We throw out historical symbols,"},{"time":425497,"text":"we rely on new, computer-aided\ndesign techniques,"},{"time":429367,"text":"and we come up with new compositions,"},{"time":431348,"text":"forms crashing into forms."},{"time":434228,"text":"This is academic and heady stuff,"},{"time":437275,"text":"it's super unpopular,"},{"time":439150,"text":"we totally alienate you."},{"time":440837,"text":"Ordinarily, the pendulum would just\nswing back into the other direction."},{"time":445048,"text":"And then, something amazing happened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448331,"text":"In 1997, this building opened."},{"time":451898,"text":"This is the Guggenheim Bilbao,\nby Frank Gehry."},{"time":456228,"text":"And this building"},{"time":457656,"text":"fundamentally changes\nthe world's relationship to architecture."},{"time":462694,"text":"Paul Goldberger said that Bilbao\nwas one of those rare moments"},{"time":466618,"text":"when critics, academics,\nand the general public"},{"time":469945,"text":"were completely united around a building."},{"time":473401,"text":"The New York Times\ncalled this building a miracle."},{"time":477160,"text":"Tourism in Bilbao increased 2,500 percent"},{"time":482866,"text":"after this building was completed."},{"time":484885,"text":"So all of a sudden, everybody\nwants one of these buildings:"},{"time":489044,"text":"L.A.,"},{"time":491633,"text":"Seattle,"},{"time":493196,"text":"Chicago,"},{"time":494824,"text":"New York,"},{"time":496552,"text":"Cleveland,"},{"time":498470,"text":"Springfield."},{"time":499737,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":500795,"text":"Everybody wants one,\nand Gehry is everywhere."},{"time":504042,"text":"He is our very first starchitect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":507989,"text":"Now, how is it possible\nthat these forms --"},{"time":512889,"text":"they're wild and radical --"},{"time":514818,"text":"how is it possible that they become\nso ubiquitous throughout the world?"},{"time":519270,"text":"And it happened because media\nso successfully galvanized around them"},{"time":524790,"text":"that they quickly taught us\nthat these forms mean culture and tourism."},{"time":531068,"text":"We created an emotional\nreaction to these forms."},{"time":534490,"text":"So did every mayor in the world."},{"time":536967,"text":"So every mayor knew\nthat if they had these forms,"},{"time":539493,"text":"they had culture and tourism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":543778,"text":"This phenomenon\nat the turn of the new millennium"},{"time":546134,"text":"happened to a few other starchitects."},{"time":548288,"text":"It happened to Zaha"},{"time":550695,"text":"and it happened to Libeskind,"},{"time":553118,"text":"and what happened\nto these elite few architects"},{"time":557756,"text":"at the turn of the new millennium"},{"time":559536,"text":"could actually start to happen\nto the entire field of architecture,"},{"time":563237,"text":"as digital media starts\nto increase the speed"},{"time":566499,"text":"with which we consume information."},{"time":569096,"text":"Because think about\nhow you consume architecture."},{"time":572429,"text":"A thousand years ago,"},{"time":573668,"text":"you would have had to have walked to\nthe village next door to see a building."},{"time":577488,"text":"Transportation speeds up:"},{"time":579142,"text":"You can take a boat, you can take a plane,\nyou can be a tourist."},{"time":582166,"text":"Technology speeds up:\nYou can see it in a newspaper, on TV,"},{"time":585087,"text":"until finally, we are all\narchitectural photographers,"},{"time":589974,"text":"and the building has become\ndisembodied from the site."},{"time":594768,"text":"Architecture is everywhere now,"},{"time":598339,"text":"and that means that\nthe speed of communication"},{"time":601477,"text":"has finally caught up\nto the speed of architecture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605409,"text":"Because architecture\nactually moves quite quickly."},{"time":607903,"text":"It doesn't take long\nto think about a building."},{"time":610635,"text":"It takes a long time to build a building,"},{"time":612812,"text":"three or four years,"},{"time":615130,"text":"and in the interim, an architect\nwill design two or eight"},{"time":618822,"text":"or a hundred other buildings"},{"time":621492,"text":"before they know if that building\nthat they designed four years ago"},{"time":625207,"text":"was a success or not."},{"time":627690,"text":"That's because there's never been\na good feedback loop in architecture."},{"time":632416,"text":"That's how we end up\nwith buildings like this."},{"time":635332,"text":"Brutalism wasn't a two-year movement,"},{"time":638296,"text":"it was a 20-year movement."},{"time":640383,"text":"For 20 years, we were producing\nbuildings like this"},{"time":644225,"text":"because we had no idea\nhow much you hated it."},{"time":648284,"text":"It's never going to happen again,"},{"time":651108,"text":"I think,"},{"time":653262,"text":"because we are living on the verge\nof the greatest revolution in architecture"},{"time":659386,"text":"since the invention of concrete,"},{"time":661779,"text":"of steel, or of the elevator,"},{"time":664257,"text":"and it's a media revolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":667072,"text":"So my theory is that when\nyou apply media to this pendulum,"},{"time":671756,"text":"it starts swinging faster and faster,"},{"time":674641,"text":"until it's at both extremes\nnearly simultaneously,"},{"time":678403,"text":"and that effectively blurs the difference\nbetween innovation and symbol,"},{"time":683395,"text":"between us, the architects,\nand you, the public."},{"time":687342,"text":"Now we can make nearly instantaneous,\nemotionally charged symbols"},{"time":693426,"text":"out of something that's brand new."}]},{"cues":[{"time":696453,"text":"Let me show you how this plays out"},{"time":698210,"text":"in a project that my firm\nrecently completed."},{"time":700829,"text":"We were hired to replace this building,\nwhich burned down."},{"time":704304,"text":"This is the center of a town\ncalled the Pines"},{"time":706797,"text":"in Fire Island in New York State."},{"time":708567,"text":"It's a vacation community."},{"time":710729,"text":"We proposed a building that was audacious,"},{"time":714506,"text":"that was different than any of the forms\nthat the community was used to,"},{"time":718181,"text":"and we were scared\nand our client was scared"},{"time":722726,"text":"and the community was scared,"},{"time":724513,"text":"so we created a series\nof photorealistic renderings"},{"time":728693,"text":"that we put onto Facebook"},{"time":730095,"text":"and we put onto Instagram,"},{"time":732245,"text":"and we let people start\nto do what they do:"},{"time":734590,"text":"share it, comment, like it, hate it."},{"time":738232,"text":"But that meant that two years\nbefore the building was complete,"},{"time":742586,"text":"it was already a part of the community,"},{"time":745938,"text":"so that when the renderings\nlooked exactly like the finished product,"},{"time":752228,"text":"there were no surprises."},{"time":754212,"text":"This building was already a part\nof this community,"},{"time":758124,"text":"and then that first summer,"},{"time":760433,"text":"when people started arriving\nand sharing the building on social media,"},{"time":764375,"text":"the building ceased to be just an edifice\nand it became media,"},{"time":769886,"text":"because these, these are not\njust pictures of a building,"},{"time":773693,"text":"they're your pictures of a building."},{"time":776527,"text":"And as you use them to tell your story,"},{"time":779838,"text":"they become part\nof your personal narrative,"},{"time":782570,"text":"and what you're doing\nis you're short-circuiting"},{"time":786142,"text":"all of our collective memory,"},{"time":788416,"text":"and you're making these charged symbols\nfor us to understand."},{"time":793187,"text":"That means we don't need\nthe Greeks anymore"},{"time":795500,"text":"to tell us what to think\nabout architecture."},{"time":798142,"text":"We can tell each other\nwhat we think about architecture,"},{"time":802191,"text":"because digital media hasn't just changed\nthe relationship between all of us,"},{"time":807986,"text":"it's changed the relationship\nbetween us and buildings."},{"time":812614,"text":"Think for a second about\nthose librarians back in Livingston."},{"time":816390,"text":"If that building was going\nto be built today,"},{"time":818829,"text":"the first thing they would do is go online\nand search \"new libraries.\""},{"time":823705,"text":"They would be bombarded by examples\nof experimentation, of innovation,"},{"time":828999,"text":"of pushing at the envelope\nof what a library can be."},{"time":832998,"text":"That's ammunition."},{"time":834846,"text":"That's ammunition\nthat they can take with them"},{"time":837205,"text":"to the mayor of Livingston,\nto the people of Livingston,"},{"time":840354,"text":"and say, there's no one answer\nto what a library is today."},{"time":844337,"text":"Let's be a part of this."},{"time":846287,"text":"This abundance of experimentation"},{"time":849177,"text":"gives them the freedom\nto run their own experiment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":854452,"text":"Everything is different now."},{"time":856664,"text":"Architects are no longer\nthese mysterious creatures"},{"time":860043,"text":"that use big words\nand complicated drawings,"},{"time":862562,"text":"and you aren't the hapless public,"},{"time":865546,"text":"the consumer that won't accept\nanything that they haven't seen anymore."},{"time":870980,"text":"Architects can hear you,"},{"time":872737,"text":"and you're not intimidated\nby architecture."},{"time":875770,"text":"That means that that pendulum\nswinging back and forth"},{"time":879176,"text":"from style to style,\nfrom movement to movement,"},{"time":882178,"text":"is irrelevant."},{"time":883680,"text":"We can actually move forward"},{"time":886304,"text":"and find relevant solutions\nto the problems that our society faces."},{"time":891757,"text":"This is the end of architectural history,"},{"time":895223,"text":"and it means that\nthe buildings of tomorrow"},{"time":898115,"text":"are going to look a lot different\nthan the buildings of today."},{"time":902389,"text":"It means that a public space\nin the ancient city of Seville"},{"time":906821,"text":"can be unique and tailored\nto the way that a modern city works."},{"time":911992,"text":"It means that a stadium in Brooklyn\ncan be a stadium in Brooklyn,"},{"time":916435,"text":"not some red-brick historical pastiche"},{"time":919221,"text":"of what we think a stadium ought to be."},{"time":922540,"text":"It means that robots are going\nto build our buildings,"},{"time":925397,"text":"because we're finally ready for the forms\nthat they're going to produce."},{"time":929842,"text":"And it means that buildings\nwill twist to the whims of nature"},{"time":933717,"text":"instead of the other way around."},{"time":936676,"text":"It means that a parking garage\nin Miami Beach, Florida,"},{"time":940304,"text":"can also be a place for sports"},{"time":942812,"text":"and for yoga"},{"time":944215,"text":"and you can even\nget married there late at night."},{"time":946818,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":947866,"text":"It means that three architects\ncan dream about swimming"},{"time":952053,"text":"in the East River of New York,"},{"time":953997,"text":"and then raise nearly\nhalf a million dollars"},{"time":956511,"text":"from a community\nthat gathered around their cause,"},{"time":959863,"text":"no one client anymore."},{"time":962765,"text":"It means that no building\nis too small for innovation,"},{"time":965690,"text":"like this little reindeer pavilion"},{"time":967912,"text":"that's as muscly and sinewy\nas the animals it's designed to observe."},{"time":973808,"text":"And it means that a building\ndoesn't have to be beautiful"},{"time":976570,"text":"to be lovable,"},{"time":977887,"text":"like this ugly little building in Spain,"},{"time":980926,"text":"where the architects dug a hole,"},{"time":983431,"text":"packed it with hay,"},{"time":984837,"text":"and then poured concrete around it,"},{"time":987194,"text":"and when the concrete dried,"},{"time":988858,"text":"they invited someone to come\nand clean that hay out"},{"time":992442,"text":"so that all that's left when it's done"},{"time":995397,"text":"is this hideous little room"},{"time":998096,"text":"that's filled with the imprints\nand scratches of how that place was made,"},{"time":1004074,"text":"and that becomes the most sublime place\nto watch a Spanish sunset."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1009658,"text":"Because it doesn't matter\nif a cow builds our buildings"},{"time":1013037,"text":"or a robot builds our buildings."},{"time":1014871,"text":"It doesn't matter how we build,\nit matters what we build."},{"time":1018899,"text":"Architects already know how\nto make buildings that are greener"},{"time":1022348,"text":"and smarter and friendlier."},{"time":1024530,"text":"We've just been waiting\nfor all of you to want them."},{"time":1028022,"text":"And finally, we're not\non opposite sides anymore."},{"time":1031957,"text":"Find an architect, hire an architect,"},{"time":1034953,"text":"work with us to design better buildings,\nbetter cities, and a better world,"},{"time":1040794,"text":"because the stakes are high."},{"time":1043635,"text":"Buildings don't just reflect our society,\nthey shape our society"},{"time":1048849,"text":"down to the smallest spaces:"},{"time":1050925,"text":"the local libraries,"},{"time":1052953,"text":"the homes where we raise our children,"},{"time":1055406,"text":"and the walk that they take\nfrom the bedroom to the bathroom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1059288,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1060412,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}